{"id": "760407", "revid": "7903804", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=760407", "title": "Davidson's", "text": "Davidson's is a Roanoke, Virginia-based chain of menswear stores. The company was founded in 1910. Its downtown location is at 412 S. Jefferson St., in a former S&amp;W Cafeteria, that it has occupied since 1964. In 2008, the location underwent a $2 million renovation. Other locations are at the Grand Pavilion in Roanoke County across from the Tanglewood Mall, and Westlake Plaza, at Smith Mountain Lake, Hardy, Virginia."}
